* Small signal NPN BJT model
* Vo = Vout = (1+beta)*Ib = (1+beta)*Re*Vin/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re)\nIb = Vin/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re)\n \nrpi = (beta+1)*V_T/Ie_Q = 230*26m/2m = 2.99k ohm\nRs = 10m\n \nGain = (1+beta)*Re*/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re) = (1+229)*3.5k/(10m+ 2.99k +230*3.5k) = 0.996 -> about 1\n \nInput impedance=Vin/i_in = Vsignal/ib = Rs + rpi + (1+beta)*Re = 10m + 2.99k+3.5k*229 =804.49k ohm\n \nOutput impedance is Re//rpi/(1+beta) = 3.5k // (2.99k/229) = 12.95 ohm
* Vo = Vout = (1+beta)*Ib = (1+beta)*Re*Vin/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re)\nIb = Vin/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re)\n \nrpi = (beta+1)*V_T/Ie_Q = 230*26m/2m = 2.99k ohm\nRs = 10m\n \nGain = (1+beta)*Re*/(Rs+rpi+(1+beta)*Re) = (1+229)*3.5k/(10m+ 2.99k +230*3.5k) = 0.996 -> about 1\n \nInput impedance=Vin/i_in = Vsignal/ib = Rs + rpi + (1+beta)*Re = 10m + 2.99k+3.5k*229 =804.49k ohm\n \nOutput impedance is Re//rpi/(1+beta) = 3.5k // (2.99k/229) = 12.95 ohm (Rs is very low so it short circuits R4 and R5)
